-- 
Zimbabwe to Hold Diamond Conference in October, Herald Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-09-21T06:03:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/zimbabwe-to-hold-diamond-conference-in-october-herald-reports.html
Zimbabwe will hold a conference
between Oct. 26 and Oct. 28 at which it will discuss ways of
adding value to the nation’s diamonds, the  Herald  said, citing
Sakiwe Ndlovu, an official at closely held producer Afrimond
Zimbabwe.  Diamond organizations expected to attend the event include
the World Diamond Council, the African Diamond Producers’
Association as well as groups from India and  Israel , the Harare-
based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  